SIMPLE: doer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Doer
<hw>Do"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Do</er>,
<pos>v. t. & i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who does; one who
performs or executes; one who is wont and ready to act; an actor; an
agent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>doers</qex> of the law shall be justified.</q> <rj><qau>
Rom. ii. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>An agent or attorney; a
factor.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Does</ent>⟦br⟧
